class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΞΕΝ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΒΑΣ̣Λ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"file":383,"uri":383,"title":384,"status":385,"editionAuthor":21,"type":387,"objectType":388,"material":392,"condition":30,"layoutDesc":396,"handNote":400,"date":414,"places":417,"geo":420,"provenance":57,"provenanceGeo":422,"country":10,"region":69,"settlement":57,"repository":423,"textLang":424,"tmNumber":30,"facsimile":426,"letterHeights":428,"publications":429,"zotero":432,"keywords":435,"html":440},"ISic004390","Fragmentary early Christian funerary inscription",{"_":386},"edited",{"_":120,"ana":121,"ref":122},{"_":389,"ana":390,"ref":391},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html",{"_":393,"ana":394,"ref":395},"marble\n                                    ","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"layout":397},{"p":398,"rs":399,"damage":30},"Remains of three lines of Greek letters, with small space to the margin at top, and vacat to the right and a roughly consistent right margin, suggesting line ends are preserved. The letters on the fourth fragment are smaller, and preserve vacat to the left suggesting line beginning. A further line is partially preserved on the fourth fragment.",{"_":34,"ana":35,"ref":36},{"lettering":401,"dimensions":402},"The letters are fairly regularly cut, with almost no serifs/terminations to the strokes, excpt for the slight extension of the apex of alpha and delta. Alpha has broken bar; omicron is slightly ovoid and full size; pi has equal length verticals; epsilon is lunate; phi is rhomboid.",[403,405,408,410],{"type":42,"l":43,"from":44,"to":44,"h":404,"unit":45},"12",{"type":42,"l":406,"from":49,"to":49,"h":407,"unit":45},"Line 2","12-14",{"type":47,"l":48,"from":44,"to":49,"h":409,"unit":45},"2",{"type":47,"l":411,"from":49,"to":412,"h":413,"unit":45},"Interlineation line 2 to 3","line3","1-2",{"_":415,"notBefore":358,"notAfter":416,"evidence":142,"precision":54},"4th century CE",400,[418,419],{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59},{"_":61,"type":62,"ref":63},[421],[66,67],[],{"_":4,"role":3,"ref":5},{"_":72,"mainLang":73,"languages":425},[72],{"n":77,"url":427,"height":79,"width":80,"desc":81,"surfaceType":82},"ISic004390_tiled.tif",[],[430,431],"À propos d’une inscription funéraire paléochrétienne de Mégara Hyblaea, 2011","Mégara Hyblaea. 7, La ville classique, hellénistique et romaine, 2018",[433,434],"DFXDQ8GT","5UHWUE4K",[436,437,438,120,389,439,108,109,110,111,108,112,113,73],"isic004390","fragmentary early christian funerary inscription",{"_":386},"marble","\u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">fragment (physical) a\u003C/span>  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"diva--interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"aa-l1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>τ]ό παιδὶον \u003Cbr id=\"aa-l2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[ὃς ἀπὲθανε] τῇ πρό \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ε\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"aa-l3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[εἰδῶν Σεπτε]μβρὶων \u003Cbr id=\"aa-l4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[ζῆσας ἔτη\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abb\">fragment (physical) b\u003C/span>  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"divb--interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"ab-l1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>φα[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"file":442,"uri":442,"title":443,"status":444,"editionAuthor":21,"type":445,"objectType":449,"material":453,"condition":30,"layoutDesc":454,"handNote":458,"date":468,"places":472,"geo":475,"provenance":57,"provenanceGeo":477,"country":10,"region":69,"settlement":57,"repository":480,"idno":481,"textLang":484,"tmNumber":30,"facsimile":486,"letterHeights":488,"publications":489,"zotero":490,"keywords":491,"html":495},"ISic004405","Small altar dedicated to Aphrodite",{"_":20},{"_":446,"ana":447,"ref":448},"dedication","#function.dedication","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":450,"ana":451,"ref":452},"altar","#object.altar","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/29.html",{"_":27,"ana":28,"ref":29},{"layout":455},{"p":456,"rs":457,"damage":30},"Three lines of Greek letters are incised into the front face, occupying most of the space between the mouldings, with a more or less consistent left margin and an uneven right margin",{"_":34,"ana":35,"ref":36},{"lettering":459,"dimensions":460},"The letters are somewhat unevenly incised. Horizontals on alpha and eta often slope down to the left; epsilon is lunate; theta is roughly circulate with a detached horizontal bar in the centre; mu is unevenly incised, with a middle stroke which does not descend all the way.",[461,464,466],{"type":42,"l":462,"from":44,"to":412,"h":463,"unit":45},"Line 1-3","3-7",{"type":47,"l":48,"from":44,"to":49,"h":465,"unit":45},"2-4",{"type":47,"l":411,"from":49,"to":412,"h":467,"unit":45},"0-2",{"_":469,"notBefore":470,"notAf